== Chicken ==

Preheat your oven to 200°C. Add the @olive oil{for the chicken}, @honey{1/2%tsp}, @red wine vinegar{1/2%tbsp}, @garlic salt{1/4%tsp}, @smoked paprika{1.5%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} to a #mixing bowl{}. Add the @British chicken thighs{4}. Mix well and massage the flavours into the chicken. Keep to one side.

> Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Halve, then remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop into 2cm chunks. Lay these in a single layer on a #baking tray{} and lay the chicken thighs flat on top. Drizzle over any remaining marinade. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until the chicken is cooked through and charred at the edges, ~{20-25%minutes} (if the pepper is charred, that's fine - extra flavour!).

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

== Couscous ==

Meanwhile, boil the @water{300%ml} in a #large saucepan{} over high heat. Add the @chicken stock pot{1/2} and stir to dissolve. Remove from the heat and add the @couscous{150%g} and the @olive oil{for the couscous}. Cover with a #lid{} or #plate{} and leave to one side for ~{10-12%minutes}. The couscous will absorb the stock.

== Minty Yogurt Dip ==

While everything cooks, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @mint{1/2}(leaves picked from stalks and finely chopped) from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks). Mix the garlic and half the mint into the @Greek style yoghurt{1} in a #bowl{} and season with a pinch of @salt{}. Keep to one side.

> If you're not keen on raw garlic, just add a tiny bit, or none at all!

== Assembly ==

Remove the top and bottom from the @cucumber{1/2} and slice into thin strips lengthways, then chop into small 1cm chunks. Zest the @lemon{1/2}, then cut into wedges. Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{} and then stir in the cucumber and the remaining mint and lemon zest. Taste and season well with salt, pepper and lemon juice if necessary.

When the chicken is cooked, transfer to a #chopping board{}. Slice the chicken into 1cm strips. Share the couscous between your bowls, top with the pepper and then the chicken. Drizzle on some of the juices from the baking tray and finish with a dollop of the minty yoghurt and some lemon wedges, for anyone that likes things extra zingy! Enjoy!